  {
    "example_image": "https://bwbopiabddpxhacfscvq.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/uploads/home_styles/modern-coastal.avif",
    "type": "interior",
    "template_id": "interior0007",
    "style_name": "Modern Coastal Style",
    "prompt": "Modern Coastal takes the breezy, beach-inspired feeling of coastal decor and updates it with cleaner lines and a more sophisticated palette. Instead of overly themed “nautical” props, it uses light, sun-washed neutrals—white, sand, soft gray—plus airy textiles like linen and cotton. Wood tones are typically pale oak or whitewashed finishes, while accents might include natural stone, rattan, and subtle ocean hues like dusty blue or seafoam green. The modern part is restraint: fewer decorative items, more negative space, and furniture with simple silhouettes. You’ll often see slipcovered sofas, wide-plank floors, and large rugs that ground the room without visual heaviness. Light is a feature—sheer curtains, reflective surfaces, and layered lighting keep the space bright even indoors. This style works well for apartments too, not just beach houses: the trick is to prioritize breathable materials and a calm palette that suggests the coast without shouting it. Modern Coastal feels open, clean, and vacation-like, but still polished enough for everyday life."
  },
  {
